Is there a reason this one needs nonempty but the others don't?

The free module / abelian group on zero generators is the zero module / abelian group, so any map out of it is injective.
However the free commutative ring on zero generators is Z (in general it's MvPolynomial over Z), which maps to quotients Z/nZ non-injectively (when n is not 1 or -1).
(It's funny I tried to construct a Unique instance on the FreeCommRing before [this commit](https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/8473/commits/366d3df31092484408b6e3cdd9844d37cc67fb3f), but Lean firmly rejected it.)
